author: COMSOL
description: 1 ampere is defined as the current in two parallel conductors of infinite length and negligible circular cross section, one meter apart, that produces a force of 2e-7 N/m. This example shows a setup of two parallel wires in the spirit of this definition with the difference that the wires have nonnegligible cross sections.
